JPMorgan Chase & Co. $2 Billion Loss under Investigation by Finkelstein Thompson LLP
Friday, 11 May 2012 12:51pm EDT
JPMorgan Chase & Co. announced that it has suffered $2 billion or more in trading losses. A May 11, 2012 Wall Street Journal article indicates the 'losses stemmed from wagers gone wrong in the bank's Chief Investment Office' and involved losses in derivative positions. Following this revelation, J.P. Morgan shares fell in value. The law firm of Finkelstein Thompson LLP is investigating claims on behalf of J.P. Morgan shareholders regarding the trading strategy and resulting losses.Â 
